annotation.TEXT: Well, that's all of the Yoshi coins, and I hope I've checked every block here...
Ooh, gotta be big to get this Yoshi coin.
And there's the pipe that I went in just a moment ago.
Oh, the PMGs can be slide-killed. Could they be slide-killed in SMB3? Actually, did they even appear in any levels that had slopes in SMB3?

Yep, it's still glitched, just like last time! Since the only enemy out here is a standard Chuck, you could safely change the sprite tileset here to be the same as inside of the cave, and then Mr. Buzzy won't look glitchy out here.
Okay, enough fooling around. Let's enter Caramel Hills 3 now.
Okay, now what happens if I take a Buzzy through the pipe here?
Hey there, stupid hit. How's it going?
Alright, let's go back and see what I skipped over, as usual.
Whoa, didn't see that mole coming.
Gah! And then I somehow screwed that up and got robbed of my deserved mushroom there!
Okay, clearing that level doesn't cause a new path to appear, but it cause me to walk up to another incomplete level that I can't enter.
This level was also Caramel Hills 3 last time.
If anyone doesn't get that, watch Marriland's Pok√©mon Emerald Nuzlocke video series.
Okay, it looks like I've found the way in.
Ah. Well, that's an obvious place to use the P-switch.
You see, when a coin is placed directly over a ? block, and that ? block is hit, it leaves behind an invisible solid block where the coin was for some reason.

It's not flammable or inflammable, but it's not supposed to be, so that's fine. It should be vulnerable to a normal stomp, a thrown weapon, a hit block, and a raccoon tail swing (or a cape spin here, since this isn't SMB3).
Obligatory replays and added sound effects.
...Assuming I can avoid taking a dumb hit somewhere...
Wow, that's a lot of turn blocks. I mean, this is no "Star World 1", but it's still a lot. I just hope I don't glitch through the floor somehow...
Alright, so I'm in an autoscrolling cloudy bonus area. (Isn't that also a thing in SMB3? Oh, but you traditionally used a hidden pink note block to access such an area.)
I'm a little surprised that I didn't glitch through the floor again there.
Whoa! It's a Piledriver Micro-Goomba! Cool!
And that lets me access Caramel Castle, which I'll be playing next time! Now, before I end the video, I want my mushroom back.
Of course, I'll want to check the other turn blocks for goodies...
It's a multi-coin block, and I've got a shell... Uh, oh.
Nah, I'll keep the cape for now.
Well, I messed that up. Maybe I could still get something going with the remaining block, but... screw it.
Oh, and there's my cape...
Heck, yeah. Goin' in a pipe and creating NeverMeltIce.
Whoa! Hey! Get back here, 1-up!

From the second "-INCOMPLETE-" tile, I can move right to get back onto the first one, and that's all. I'm not sure what the deal is with the paths there, but at least it doesn't appear that I can get permanently stuck...
Well, there's the exit pipe. Oh! I just thought of something, but I can't check it right this instant... It involves a Buzzy Beetle in this level, but I think I already killed them all.
Oh, no. I'm not going to let myself glitch through the floor again...
Demo count: 2
Really? A multi-coin block there? Without a cape, there's no way I can get a large number of coins from it, and it's too low to block clone...
This could be annoying. I've gotta find the breakable ones to reach that Yoshi coin.

Nope, pausing doesn't work here. In the original SMB3, pausing the game made all sprites disappear, which would obviously give away a Piledriver Micro-Goomba's position. But, in SMW, sprites don't vanish when you pause. However, I can easily tell which blocks are PMGs here anyway.
GAAAMMMEEE!!!
This level was also Caramel Hills 4 last time.
May as well get the cape while I'm here too.
Man, I sure am taking this shell quite far. I wonder if I can keep it until the end...
That opens Caramel Hills 4. However, I'm going to quickly go back through channel 3 again to check that one thing...
And now to gracefully return to the land below...
I can go in this pipe. Oh, but this bonus room has changed a bit from last time.
Oh, even more turn blocks? And they're covering a pit this time... Okay, screw it. I'm not going to check every one of those. (If there is something of value in any of them, let me know!)
Alright, now let's not go glitching through the floor again...
Alright, I think I got one more level in me today, so let's do Caramel Hills 4 now!
A couple of the ? block rows have been removed, and there have been coins added. And, with those coins comes a glitch, too. How nice!
BGM: Adventures of Lolo - Main Theme
Huh. I wonder why there was that one mole to the right of the goal. If I had hit the goal right away, I might not have even seen it at all.
Well, I failed at all of my attempts to block clone here, but I also got a perfectly legit perfect! Although, there were only three rows of ? blocks instead of five, but the perfect is still cool.
Ha! Don't think I didn't see you there, PMG!
So many turn blocks. If only I had a cape...
And, that dumb hit occurred just after I'd collected a power up, which sucks...
Meh. I'm not too concerned with killing every single enemy. If one manages to elude me and I don't feel any hatred towards it, I may just let it go.
COINS!!!
Or, I suppose a small-sized plumber could make use of those ice blocks over there to get to it.
Oh, come on! I was totally at the goal! Why'd I have to be dumb there? Okay, I can still get my bigness back if I just go back for a shell and bring it to the goal...
Well, that totally just happened. Let me quickly get back to where I was...
Gotta check every turn block...
What the? Did that turn block not react to being struck? Huh, so you've included some of those unbreakable solid turn blocks here...
Alright, so Caramel Secret it is!
Ha! You cannot escape from me!

So, I guess that means the shell's kill combo only resets when I voluntarily let go of it (by putting it down or kicking it). (I wonder if a shell's kill combo can be preserved that way after being taken through a pipe...)
Alright, see you next time!
I wonder what this P-switch is for. It's not like there are huge pyramids that I could turn into coins nearby, are there?

Argh! And I took a dumb hit somewhere! Oh, interesting. Judging by the sound that the shell made when it hit the Swooper that hit me, I guess the shell's kill combo doesn't reset from me grabbing it if it dislodges from me because I got hit.
Argh! I got too trigger-happy and fried a guy that I could've gotten a cape from! D'oh!

Yo, duders! Welcome back to more Lunar Legends! Now, which of these two levels will I be entering next? (Huh, that looks like a slightly odd path that I'm walking between Caramel Hills 2 and Caramel Secret...)
Block clipping FTW!
ZAZAZAZAZA
Yeah, I was in too much of a hurry to check every turn block, and I even knew that it was possible for that to happen, too...
Oh, god. What is this structure that I'm going to have to disect?

Umm... That's weird. Okay, from the "-INCOMPLETE-" spot that I landed on after clearing Caramel Secret, I can move left to return to Caramel Secret, or move up, which causes me to go up, then left, then down, onto another "-INCOMPLETE-" tile.
BGM: Pilotwings SNES - Rocket Belt
Okay, there's the vine that I took up to coin heaven earlier, so let's move on.
Huh. I was half-expecting to crush something under my feet as I was landing there. (How can I "half-expect" something?)
Let's find out...
Correctly predicted that was a multi-coin block.
To be continued...
